import SigmaR.StandingAlgebra_FormalCore

/-!
###############################################################################
# Autonomy Valuation Contract
###############################################################################

This file defines the governing interpretive rules of the
Autonomy Valuation sub-layer in SigmaR.

Autonomy valuation:
• evaluates effective freedom from structural constraint,
  not consent or moral authorization
• is downstream of perception, capacity, transformability,
  risk, exit cost, and coupling
• supports both internal and external autonomy agreement
• incorporates aggregation, loss, erosion, fragility,
  propagation, amplification, and dampening
• allows irreversibility, hysteresis, thresholds,
  and collapse to be represented structurally
• encodes autonomy-progress as a boundary condition,
  not a preference or selection rule
• treats omission of available autonomy-progress as a
  structural constraint, not moral fault
• does not imply consent, legitimacy, authority,
  or moral judgment
• does not authorize intervention or coercive action
• respects Independence, Monotonicity, Admissibility,
  and ResponseSemantics
• is always explicitly scoped

This file introduces no axioms.
###############################################################################
-/

namespace SigmaR

/--
The Autonomy Valuation layer is governed by an explicit
interpretive contract defining its scope and limits.
-/
constant AutonomyValuationContract : Prop

end SigmaR
